s/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-20t16:47:18z","updated_at":"2013-11-20t16:47:18z","body":"> this is true, /var/www/owncloud/config/config.php does not exist. however, autoconfig.php does in the same directory as the owncloud.postinst script uses that name instead of config.php. the second set of error messages is due to mysql not being executed properly as the installation script could not extract the login information from the aforementioned config.php.\r\n\r\nsounds like the autosetup could not have been completed. the autosetup process will create the config.php based on autoconfig.php. symlinking autoconfig really won't help at all.\r\n\r\ncould you provide the whole log?\r\n\r\nhas owncloud been installed before? if so, how was it removed.\r\n\r\nwas mysql been installed before? did /etc/mysql.secret exist?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/28984759","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-28984759","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":28984759,"user":{"login":"mbunkus","id":414282,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f4f540311753eea54e57545752d4f7239.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus","html_url":"https://github.com/mbunkus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-21t13:38:38z","updated_at":"2013-11-21t13:38:38z","body":"i can re-install and provide the whole log, yes, but i will have to modify it in order to remove the customer's name. i'll simply replace those occurrences with xxxxx.\r\n\r\nowncloud has been installed via the appstore for the first time in that whole ucs domain. this did not work, as i've written above. so i've uninstalled it again, tried again with the appstore, again no joy. then i installed it again for the third time from the console with `apt-get install owncloud-unsupported` (i also tried the supported package first, no difference).\r\n\r\nthe packages have been removed with the usual `apt-get purge owncloud…` (i listed all package names including `owncloud` in the name that had been installed).\r\n\r\nmysql has been installed along with the owncloud package when i first installed it via the appstore. `/etc/mysql.secret` does exist, and i've verified that the password it contains is the one that can be used with mysql's `root` user in order to connect.\r\n\r\ni will add a link to the log made just now without `config.php` present before the package is installed in a bit."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/28985188","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-28985188","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":28985188,"user":{"login":"mbunkus","id":414282,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f4f540311753eea54e57545752d4f7239.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus","html_url":"https://github.com/mbunkus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-21t13:46:02z","updated_at":"2013-11-21t13:46:02z","body":"here's the log: https://www.linet-services.de/~mbunkus/owncloud-ucs-ticket5913-install-log.txt"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29292153","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-29292153","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":29292153,"user":{"login":"blizzz","id":2184312,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fca03acec6deadf508b75eb0cf9ba036c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz","html_url":"https://github.com/blizzz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-26t13:34:04z","updated_at":"2013-11-26t13:34:04z","body":"> i can re-install and provide the whole log, yes, but i will have to modify it in order to remove the customer's name. i'll simply replace those occurrences with xxxxx.\r\n\r\nthe original log would have been more interesting. here its visible that an owncloud instance was already installed. if done properly, it's not an issue, but otherwise it can become one. please see http://doc.owncloud.org/server/5.0/admin_manual/installation/installation_ucs.html#reinstallation\r\n\r\n> owncloud has been installed via the appstore for the first time in that whole ucs domain. this did not work, as i've written above. so i've uninstalled it again, tried again with the appstore, again no joy. then i installed it again for the third time from the console with `apt-get install owncloud-unsupported` (i also tried the supported package first, no difference).\r\n\r\non a plain installation it should work, this is tested by both univention and us.\r\n\r\n> the packages have been removed with the usual `apt-get purge owncloud…` (i listed all package names including `owncloud` in the name that had been installed).\r\n\r\nsee upper link. purge will not delete data, you need to take care of it manually."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29294979","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-29294979","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":29294979,"user":{"login":"mbunkus","id":414282,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f4f540311753eea54e57545752d4f7239.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus","html_url":"https://github.com/mbunkus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-26t14:14:56z","updated_at":"2013-11-26t14:14:56z","body":"the original installation was done via the appstore, assuming it would \"just work\". it didn't, hence i can only provide logs from subsequent tries.\r\n\r\nbefore i tried to install owncloud via the appstore it hadn't been installed before.\r\n\r\ni've read the re-installation instructions, even before creating the log i linked to above, but the database wasn't even present after having purged the package. therefore there was no database to drop.\r\n\r\nhave you ever tried setting it up on any server whose role was not univention domain master? in our case we're installing it on a univention domain backup.\r\n\r\ni will try to reproduce this in two newly set-up virtual machines and get back to you."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30122965","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-30122965","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":30122965,"user":{"login":"mbunkus","id":414282,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f4f540311753eea54e57545752d4f7239.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus","html_url":"https://github.com/mbunkus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-09t11:03:50z","updated_at":"2013-12-09t11:03:50z","body":"in freshly installed virtual machines installation does work. after giving a user access to owncloud in the univention management console i can log in as that user as well as the user `owncloudadmin` with the password from `/etc/owncloudadmin.secret`.\r\n\r\na last question before i close this: is it normal that i only have one app (files) available after logging in? this concerns both the normal user and `owncloudadmin`. as `owncloudadmin` i can see other other apps that are enabled/disabled, but none of those that i would expect to see after my own private use of owncloud: no calendar, no photos, no music etc.\r\n\r\nsee http://www.linet-services.de/~mbunkus/owncloud-apps.png"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30123456","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-30123456","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":30123456,"user":{"login":"mbunkus","id":414282,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f4f540311753eea54e57545752d4f7239.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus","html_url":"https://github.com/mbunkus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-09t11:12:23z","updated_at":"2013-12-09t11:12:23z","body":"ah you have to install the package `owncloud-unsupported` manually afterwards. alright, closing."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30124779","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-30124779","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":30124779,"user":{"login":"mbunkus","id":414282,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f4f540311753eea54e57545752d4f7239.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"b009648d18d58ddd4c69351689f5c7ec","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus","html_url":"https://github.com/mbunkus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mbunkus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-09t11:34:57z","updated_at":"2013-12-09t11:34:57z","body":"found the issue. yes, it's a bug in `owncloud.postrm`. on the system on which the installation fails the environment variable `http_proxy` is set. this is expected behaviour. however, your call `wget -q --delete-after http://localhost/owncloud/upgrade.php` will also use said proxy, and the proxy will then not be able to find the site. the result is that owncloud is not set up, and `config.php` is not created, hence all the errors i've pasted above.\r\n\r\nplease change said `wget` call to use `--no-proxy`. unsetting `http_proxy` before running `apt-get install owncloud owncloud-unsupported` solved it for me as well."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30128216","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5913#issuecomment-30128216","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5913","id":30128216,"user":{"login":"blizzz","id":2184312,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fca03acec6deadf508b75eb0cf9ba036c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"1898b25a9cb3aa1a0f0febd1359910b9","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz","html_url":"https://github.com/blizzz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blizzz/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-09t12:31:12z","updated_at":"2013-12-09t12:31:12z","body":"not sure i would have found this issue – thank you a lot! will be fixed with the ucs packages for next release."}]